h4 Dismissible
p.-text
  | To allow users to dismiss an alert, apply the class <code>-dismiss</code> to a Base or Titled Bubble Alert
  | and insert a dismiss button <code>m-alert__dismiss-button</code>.
.example.-mb3
  .-p1
    .m-alert.-m2.-dismiss.-success
      i.m-alert__icon.a-icon.icon-circle-check
      .m-alert__content
        p.m-alert__text This is a base dismissible success alert
      button(class='m-alert__dismiss-button a-btn -icon -close -sm')
        .a-btn__content
          i.a-icon.icon-x
    .m-alert.-m2.-dismiss.-success
      i.m-alert__icon.a-icon.icon-circle-check
      .m-alert__content
        p.m-alert__title Success
        p.m-alert__text This is a titled dismissible success alert
      button(class='m-alert__dismiss-button a-btn -icon -close -sm')
        .a-btn__content
          i.a-icon.icon-x
  :code(lang="html")
    <!-- Success Base -->
    <div class="m-alert -success -dismiss" role="alert">
      <i class="m-alert__icon a-icon icon-circle-check"></i>
      <div class="m-alert__content">
        <p class="m-alert__text">This is a base dismissible success alert</p>
      </div>
      <button class="m-alert__dismiss-button a-btn -icon -close -sm">
        <div class="a-btn__content">
          <i class="a-icon icon-x"></i>
        </div>
      </button>
    </div>
    <!-- Success Titled -->
    <div class="m-alert -success -dismiss" role="alert">
      <i class="m-alert__icon a-icon icon-circle-check"></i>
      <div class="m-alert__content">
        <p class="m-alert__title">Success</p>
        <p class="m-alert__text">This is a titled dismissible success alert</p>
      </div>
      <button class="m-alert__dismiss-button a-btn -icon -close -sm">
        <div class="a-btn__content">
          <i class="a-icon icon-x"></i>
        </div>
      </button>
    </div>

h4 Actionable
p.-text
  | While <code>m-alert__actions</code> can be added to any Base or Titled Alert, alert actions are best suited for Base or Titled Alerts with the size class <code>-lg</code>.
  | Large Alerts have extra <code>m-alert</code> padding, a larger <code>m-alert__icon</code>, and a larger <code>m-alert__dismiss-button</code>.
.example.-mb3
  .-p1
    .m-alert.-m2.-success.-lg
      i.m-alert__icon.a-icon.icon-circle-check.-sm--2
      .m-alert__content
        p.m-alert__title Success
        p.m-alert__text This is a large titled dismissible success alert
        div.m-alert__actions
          button.a-btn.-lg.-dark.-outline Secondary action
          button.a-btn.-lg.-primary Primary action
      button(class='m-alert__dismiss-button a-btn -icon -close')
        .a-btn__content
          i.a-icon.icon-x
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="m-alert -success -lg" role="alert">
      <i class="m-alert__icon a-icon icon-circle-check -sm--2"></i>
      <div class="m-alert__content">
        <p class="m-alert__title">Success</p>
        <p class="m-alert__text">This is a large success alert</p>
        <div class="m-alert__actions">
          <button class="a-btn -lg -dark -outline">Secondary action</button>
          <button class="a-btn -lg -primary">Primary action</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <button class="m-alert__dismiss-button a-btn -icon -close">
        <div class="a-btn__content">
          <i class="a-icon icon-x"></i>
        </div>
      </button>
    </div>

h3 Banner
p.-text
  | For prominent page level alerts, apply the class <code>-banner</code> to <code>m-alert</code>.
  | Banner alerts are commonly presented above or below the Header component and are used for scenarios
  | such as reminding new users to confirm their email address or notifying users when they are experiencing connectivity issues.
  | Banner alerts include a bottom border by default. If the border contrast conflicts with surrounding elements, it can be removed by
  | applying the class <code>-borderless</code> to <code>m-alert</code>.

